Customize Charts with Chart Properties

Bar Charts

Create a Horizontal Bar Chart

Use a horizontal bar chart to compare values across one or more categories.

In the lens, click  and then select the Bar chart type.
Add one or more measures to the Bar Length field.
Add one or more dimensions to analyze the measures by in the Bars field.
To rank the records and see the highest or lowest values, click the down arrow next to the measure and sort the results.

Create a Stacked Column Chart

Use a stacked column chart to compare parts of a whole and show values across one or more categories.

In the lens, click  and then select the Stacked Column chart type.
Add the Sum of Amount measure to the Bar Length field.
Add one or more dimensions to analyze the measures by in the Bars field.
To rank the records and see the highest or lowest values, click the down arrow next to the measure and sort the results.
